            <title>[LU-11140] unassume cl page upon write error</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11140</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;commit b7d38ece00135e74a627a9702d6dadff10c3c89d&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9618&quot; title=&quot;Connect readahead to prep_partial_page to improve small (&amp;lt; 1 page) write performance&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9618&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9618&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; clio: Use readahead for partial page write&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    introduced a regression that we might miss to unassume&lt;br/&gt;
    cl page when write error happen, this could make&lt;br/&gt;
    following panic happen:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    treError: 18584:0:(cl_page.c:443:cl_page_owner_clear())&lt;br/&gt;
    ASSERTION( page-&amp;gt;cp_owner-&amp;gt;ci_owned_nr &amp;gt; 0 ) failed:&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;4569800.103708&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; LustreError:&lt;br/&gt;
    18584:0:(cl_page.c:443:cl_page_owner_clear()) LBUG&lt;/p&gt;</description>
